Here's how the API endpoints are organized:

### `src/routes/index.js` (Base Routes)
```javascript
import express from 'express';
const router = express.Router();

router.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ message: 'Welcome to the API' });
});

router.get('/health', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ status: 'ok' });
});

router.post('/data', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ received: true });
});

export default router;
```

### `src/routes/users.js` (User CRUD)
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const router = express.Router();
const User = require('../models/User');

// GET /          - Get all users
// GET /:id       - Get single user by ID
```

### `src/routes/api.js` (Authentication)
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const router = express.Router();
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');
const authMiddleware = require('../middleware/auth');

router.post('/login', async (req, res) => {
  // Login endpoint - accepts email/password, returns JWT token
});
```

### Summary of Available Routes

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/` | Welcome message |
| GET | `/health` | Health check |
| POST | `/data` | Submit data |
| GET | `/users` | Get all users |
| GET | `/users/:id` | Get user by ID |
| POST | `/api/login` | User login (returns JWT) |

Note: I wasn't able to retrieve the full content of `src/routes/auth.js`, but the project appears to have user management and JWT-based authentication.

